snippet.title: Predictions for 2022 (published in 1922)
snippet.description:
What did people in 1922 imagine life today would be like?  This newspaper article from May 7, 1922 will give you all the answers.

Isn't it fun to read past predictions of the future? It's not always all about flying cars and the like. Some of the issues discussed in such predictions are very thought-provoking. It's especially heartbreaking to learn that we have seriously underdelivered on basic topics. However, it's not all doom and gloom. There's always something to laugh about, too!

Please let us know in the comments if you enjoy this type of content. We'll make sure to bring you more of it!

Check out our playlist of random 100-year-old news from 1922 :)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NoECLPv8TGQ&list=PLCetdzsqiVppsH0N5lvAUgmMjweh5V6_h

Source:
The New York herald. [volume] (New York, N.Y.), 07 May 1922. Chronicling America: Historic American Newspapers. Lib. of Congress.

snippet.title: Μικρασιάτες Πρόσφυγες στην Ελλάδα πριν και μετά το 1922
snippet.description:
Οι μικρασιάτες πρόσφυγες αποτέλεσαν το 1/5 του πληθυσμού της Ελλάδας και η αποκατάστασή τους ήταν ένα ανεπανάληπτο επίτευγμα.

Η Μαριλένα Κατσίμη μαζί με τον ιστορικό Νίκο Ανδριώτη θα περπατήσουν σε προσφυγικές γειτονιές του Μεσοπολέμου και με τη βοήθεια πολύτιμου αρχειακού υλικού θα προσπαθήσουν να κατανοήσουμε πόσο μεγάλη τομή αποτέλεσε για την Ελλάδα η έλευση των Μικρασιατών προσφύγων.

Η καταστροφή της Σμύρνης το 1922 υπήρξε μια εθνική τραγωδία, η οποία όμως πλούτισε την Ελλάδα σε όλα τα επίπεδα. Ο όρος «πρόσφυγας» από τη Μικρά Ασία έχει στην ελληνική κοινωνία σήμερα ένα ιδιαίτερα θετικό πρόσημο.

Δεν ήταν όμως πάντα έτσι. Σε αυτόν τον περίπατο θα μιλήσουμε για την υποδοχή και τη συμβίωση γηγενών και προσφύγων και τις μεταξύ τους σχέσεις. 

Παρόλο που οι Μικρασιάτες ήταν Έλληνες, ο συνειρμός του όρου «πρόσφυγας» είχε αρνητική χροιά καθ όλη τη διάρκεια του Μεσοπολέμου μέχρι και τη δεκαετία του ΄50 που αυτό σταδιακά αλλάζει.

Η όσμωση των δύο ομάδων, καθυστέρησε αλλά επέφερε μία νέα κοινωνική και πολιτισμική πραγματικότητα και διαμόρφωσε τελικά τη σύγχρονη ελληνική ταυτότητα.

Η εκπομπή συνεργάζεται με το Εθνικό Ίδρυμα Ερευνών, τα Πανεπιστήμια Αθηνών και Παντείου, καθώς και με δεκάδες άλλους φορείς.

Παρουσίαση-αρχισυνταξία: Μαριλένα Κατσίμη, Πιέρρος Τζανετάκος
Σκηνοθεσία: Έλενα Λαλοπούλου
Διεύθυνση παραγωγής: Ελένη Ντάφλου
Διεύθυνση φωτογραφίας: Γιώργος Πουλίδης
______
Δείτε κι άλλα ντοκιμαντέρ Ελληνικής παραγωγής από την λίστα:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLpnQ5zyDm4s6fl8KSCapHKqym47Dzquiz
______

snippet.title: Charlie Parr | "1922 Blues" | Western AF
snippet.description:
Western AF Present Charlie Parr | "1922 Blues" 

Charlie Parr’s music seems to have always been around. In particular we could never get the sort of driving guitar of 1922 Blues out of our heads. It was a real honor to be able to shoot with Charlie, and to get this song feels like we’ve really made it. This song has been on just about every one of Brian's playlist for 10 years.

We caught up with Charlie at the Kinney Family Farm in Fort Collins, CO. The Kinney family is half the magic that makes up the Cloverlick Banjo Shop. Beyond being great friends, they are always an open door for us when we need a location to shoot. They make a damn fine banjo too.

snippet.title: What does the 1922 Committee do and who is in it?
snippet.description:
The 1922 Committee is back in the headlines amid suggestions it could force Boris Johnson to resign as prime minister if he doesn’t step down of his own accord.

But what exactly is it, and how does it work?

The committee, consisting of all Conservative backbench MPs, meets weekly while parliament is in session and provides a way for backbenchers to co-ordinate and discuss their views independently of frontbenchers.

/// SOBRE O VÍDEO
Na primeira metade do século XX, um grupo de artistas, influenciado pelas vanguardas europeias, procurou incorporar às artes do Brasil inovações que vinham da Europa. A ideia era ressignificar o que aprenderam para produzirem, a partir daí, obras que tivessem de fato a cara do Brasil.

Assim nasceu o Modernismo no Brasil, que envolveu artistas de todas as áreas: pintura, escultura, literatura e música.

Embora não tenha sido a primeira exposição de arte modernista no Brasil, a Semana de Arte Moderna consagrou o movimento no país. Em 1922, em São Paulo, ocorreu a Semana de Arte Moderna, em São Paulo, reunindo artistas das artes visuais, da literatura e da música.

O principal objetivo do evento era promover a cultura e arte locais, desvencilhando-se cada vez mais do contexto artístico europeu e criando uma identidade artística e cultural que tivesse “a cara” do Brasil. Inicialmente a Semana de Arte Moderna seria apenas parte da programação da comemoração do centenário da Independência do Brasil. Entretanto, a repercussão e o acolhimento surpreenderam a todos de tal forma que o evento foi realizado no Theatro Municipal de São Paulo.

A professora Camila te explica esse movimento e o cenário em que estava envolto na época. 

Dúvidas? Deixa nos comentários. ;)

snippet.title: Clip CANTE JONDO, GRANADA 1922, de José Sánchez-Montes | Panorama Andaluz
snippet.description: Granada, 1922. Nada menos que Manuel de Falla y Federico García Lorca organizan un Concurso del Cante Jondo. Falla, que sueña cada noche con los cantos ancestrales que su nana le cantaba, teme la desaparición del flamenco. Mezclando imagen real y animación, este relato (basado en los trabajos del historiador José Vallejo) traza una breve historia del flamenco a partir de su situación hace cien años. Con la participación Esperanza Fernández, Paco Jarana, Alfredo Tejada, Sergio Gómez "El Colorao", Marina Heredia, Alicia Morales, Jaime Heredia "El Parrón", Antonio Gómez "El Turry", José Fermín Fernández, José Quevedo "Bolita", Álvaro Martinete, y Antonio Molina "Jony", además del testimonio de Enrique Morente.

snippet.title: 9 février 1922
snippet.description:
Aujourd’hui même, il y a 100 ans, près de 500 femmes se sont rendues au parlement de Québec pour demander d’accorder aux femmes le droit de voter et d’êtres candidates aux élections provinciales.

Pour l'occasion, l'Assemblée nationale vous présente le document 9 février 1922 qui retrace cette histoire surprenante de résilience et de persévérance.

Vous aimeriez en découvrir plus? L’histoire se déploie également dans une exposition qui allie archives, contenus audios et œuvres d’art! À voir dès maintenant au pavillon d’accueil de l’Assemblée nationale! 

En savoir plus : http://www.assnat.qc.ca/fr/visiteurs/programmation-citoyenne/9-fevrier-2022-elles-marchent-vers-le-parlement.html

Assemblée nationale du Québec : https://www.assnat.qc.ca​​​

Droits d'utilisation des archives télévisuelles de l'Assemblée nationale du Québec. Toute reproduction, en tout ou en partie, sous quelque forme que ce soit, est interdite sans l'autorisation de l'Assemblée nationale du Québec.

#assnat​​​ #assembléenationale​​​ #9février1922

snippet.title: 1922 Silver Dollar History
snippet.description:

It was produced at the Philadelphia Mint in 'high relief', and was graded with a PR-65 rating. 

Read more about this amazing, and beautifully designed coin here: 
https://atticcapital.com/1922-silver-dollar-value/

snippet.title: Habemus Papam | compilation 1922-2013
snippet.description:
1. Pius XI | Achille Ratti 6 February 1922

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum Cardinalem Achillem Ratti, qui sibi nomen imposuit Pius Undecimus

2. Pius XII | Eugenio Pacelli 2 March 1939

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Eugenium Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Pacelli, qui sibi nomen imposuit Pium

3. John XXIII | Angelo Giuseppe Roncalli 
28 October 1958

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Angelum Josephum Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Roncalli, qui sibi nomen imposuit Ioannis Vigesimi Tertii

4. Paul VI | Giovanni Battista Montini
 21 June 1963

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum et reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Ioannem Baptistam Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Montini, qui sibi nomen imposuit Paulum Sextum

5. John Paul I | Albino Luciani 
26 August 1978

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Albinum Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Luciani, qui sibi nomen imposuit Ioannis Pauli Primi

6. John Paul II | Karol Wojtyła 
16 October 1978

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Carolum Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Wojtyła, qui sibi nomen imposuit Ioannis Pauli

7. Benedict XVI | Joseph Ratzinger 
19 April 2005

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Iosephum Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Ratzinger, qui sibi nomen imposuit Benedicti Decimi Sexti

8. Francis | Jorge Mario Bergoglio 
13 March 2013

Annuntio vobis gaudium magnum: Habemus Papam! Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum Dominum, Dominum Georgium Marium Sanctæ Romanæ Ecclesiæ Cardinalem Bergoglio, qui sibi nomen imposuit Franciscum

snippet.title: Paris in Springtime - c.1922 | AI Enhanced Colorized Film w/sound
snippet.description:
Time travel back 100 years to the Paris markets on April 20th 1922. AI colorized and upscaled to 4k 60 fps clarity with added sound for an immersive experience.

Filmed along the Bouquinistes (book stalls) and Paris Flea markets, Les Halles. Today these same stalls ply their trade along the banks of the Seine.  We also glimpse various artists at work along the embankment.

Using AI neural networks, this silent film is now enhanced to 4K 60fps and with an immersive soundtrack.

Published by GlamourDaze 
by kind permission of the University of South Carolina.
AI enhancement by GlamourDaze.com

Colorized using Deep Exemplar-based Video Colorization
https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.06587

Filmed on April 20th, 1922.
Springtime in Paris - outtakes 
(Fox News Story A0609.) Fox Movietone News Collection. 
Moving Image Research Collections.
University of South Carolina.
https://digital.tcl.sc.edu/digital/collection/MVTN/id/3063/rec/1

snippet.title: Joe Biden Forgets Which Century He's In: “In 1922…”
snippet.description: President Joe Biden appeared to forget which century he was in during a campaign speech over the weekend, referring to life “in 1922.” “Look, in 1922, the price for one blood pressure drug that millions of Medicare patients — beneficiaries rely on went up one — went up by 500 percent,” he said, without correcting himself.

snippet.title: Charlie Parr teaches me 1922 Blues | How to play 1922 Blues in 3 MINUTES
snippet.description:
Charlie Parr popped back in the studio, but this time to show me how to play 1922 blues! This is a rapid-fire look-see into Charlie's picking patterns and chord voicings used in 1922 blues. Stay tuned for another video where we talk about Charlies' approach to writing 1922 blues/song writing in general!
